help house training a puppy king charles spaniel pup now months old and house training is getting nowhere i've tried praising him when he does his business outside and have started going 'grrrr naughty boy' when he does it inside but he still doesn't appear to know right from wrong getting desperate what do i do as for pooping puppies have a reflex to have to poop about minutes or so right after eating then again about minutes later this will help avoid accidents in the house when you take him outside to use the bathroom make sure you take him to the same part of the yard everytime so he will know that that's the spot he's suppose to go potty when he goes where he suppose to continue with the praising but also give him a small treat puppies don't understand praise as well as older dogs but they definitely understand treats also trying to get him use to a command such as go potty or go pee pee will help shorten the time you spend outside waiting for him to go to the bathroom if he does have an accident in the house scolding him isn't the best idea because to him he's getting attention even though you know it's negative attention for a puppy it's all the same instead when you catch him in the act immediately take him outside to his area of the yard when you can't watch him or if you're not home try crating him if none of this helps seek some advise from your veterinarian they may feel he has behavioral issues that may need special training and in some cases certain medication hope this helps Housebreaking Dog training Crate training Dog Toilet humour Fancy rat Theory of conduct Fecal incontinence Ron and Fez Hamster Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Guinea pig Main characters of Fullmetal Alchemist Humphrey Bogart Singlish Socialization Shaggy dog story Pitaten Zoophilia Good Times Prostate cancer Scooby-Doo Milton H. Erickson Friends English Springer Spaniel Procrastination Brian Griffin Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism Lady and the Tramp Tag First Battle of the Atlantic